<p>I have seen in a lot of places that a resource class in a dropwizard project has methods for GET and POST. These methods then access data from the database using the DAO and return back a json </p>  <pre><code>public class DropwizardResource {  private DropwizardDAO ddaoo;  public DropwizardResource (DropwizardDAO ddao) {     this.ddao = ddao; }  @GET @Timed @UnitOfWork public List&lt;String&gt; getAllResources() {     return ddao.findAll();     } } </code></pre>  <p>Is it advisable to have a resource initialized with other clients for some other service and then have the json returned by manual conversion? public class DropwizardResource {</p>  <pre><code>private nonDbClient ddaoo;  public DropwizardResource (nonDbClient ddao) {     this.ddao = ddao; }  @GET @Timed @UnitOfWork public List&lt;String&gt; getAllResources() {     return toJson(ddao.findAll());     } } </code></pre>